\subsubsection*{Survival analysis}

The {\bf R} package {\tt eha} \citep{eha, ehar12} is used, and the
explanatory variables are almost the same as in the Poisson regression
analysis. The difference is that instead of {\tt mBirthdate}, the
{\tt childBirthdate} is used (no big difference), and a new variable, {\tt mAge}, is introduced. It is categorized into three-year intervals. Other covariates, {\tt parity},  etc. are omitted, since they do not contribute much to the model. 

